  <title>Adjust the contrast</title>

<p>You can adjust the contrast of windows and buttons so that they're easier to see. This is not the same as <link xref="power-brighter">changing the brightness of the whole screen</link>; only parts of the <em>user interface</em> will change.</p>

  <steps>
    <item><p>Click your name on the top bar and select <gui>System Settings</gui>.</p></item>
    <item><p>Open <gui>Universal Access</gui>.</p></item>
    <item><p>Under <gui>Display</gui> select the <gui>Contrast</gui> that best suits your needs. <gui>Low</gui> will make things less vivid, for example.</p></item>
  </steps>
 <note style="tip">
 <p>You can quickly change the contrast by clicking the <link xref="a11y-icon">universal access menu</link> on the top bar and selecting <gui>Enhance contrast in colours </gui>.</p>
 </note>
